<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-10-17T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-10-17T11:00:00-05:00" n="562" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d562">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/227: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-17T12:00:00-04:00">October
                                    17, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>219. If after considering my telegram No. 218, October 16, 9 p.m., you
                            are inclined to grant recognition in the immediate future, please give
                            me preliminary advice of your decision in order that I may send you a
                            final opinion on the political situation. Some people feel that this is
                            a very critical week for the present regime and for this reason it may
                            be well to await developments and withhold a definite decision until the
                            first of next week.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>